# ============================================================================
# Cloudflare Workers Static Assets — custom response headers (admin console).
#
# Deployed project: abhinaya-cinemas-admin  →  admin.abhinayacinemas.com
# This file is copied from app/public/ into app/dist/ by the Vite build and
# parsed by Workers at deploy time. It is NOT served as an asset itself.
#
# Why only /assets/* is listed
# ----------------------------
# Workers Static Assets ALREADY sends the correct default for the SPA shell
# and every client-side route:
#     Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate   (+ ETag)
# i.e. index.html is always revalidated, so new builds ship immediately and a
# device can never get permanently stuck on an old shell. We deliberately do
# NOT restate that here: Cloudflare JOINS the values of every matching rule
# with a comma, so a catch-all "/*" rule would collide with the rule below and
# emit a malformed "max-age=0 ... , max-age=31536000" Cache-Control. Listing
# only the non-overlapping /assets/* path keeps the header clean.
#
# Vite emits content-hashed, immutable bundles (and sourcemaps) into /assets/
# — the filename changes on every meaningful edit — so these are safe to cache
# for a year. This both speeds up repeat loads and lets the edge serve them
# without revalidation, while the always-revalidated shell still controls which
# asset hashes a client requests.
# ============================================================================

/assets/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
